From: Jake Teton-Landis <just.1.jake@gmail.com>
Date: Wed, 8 Jul 2026 14:06:21 -0400
Subject: [PATCH 1/2] Signal seam: pass-start/pass-commit/mutation-window
 emits, lane facts provider, pinned-lane scheduling

A minimal seam for external signal runtimes. React reports lanes as opaque
numbers at render-pass start and per-root commit, brackets the DOM mutation
phase, answers which lane an external write issued right now would take, and
lets the runtime schedule a corrective update pinned to a live batch's lane.
Batch identity and write classification live entirely in the runtime.
